.CD "pr \(en print a file"
.SX "pr\fR [\fB\(enMfnt\fR]\fR [\fB\(enh \fIn\fR]  [\fB\(enl \fIn\fR]  [\fB\(enw \fIn\fR] [\fB\(en\fRcolumns\fR] [\fB+\fIpage\fR] [\fIfile\fR] ..."
.FL "\(enM" "Use MINIX style line number"
.FL "\(enf" "Do not fold long lines"
.FL "\(enh" "Take next argument as page header"
.FL "\(enl" "Sets page length in lines"
.FL "\(enn" "Number the output lines"
.FL "\(ent" "Do not print page header or trailer"
.FL "\(enw" "Sets line length in characters"
.EX "pr \(enw85 \(enl60 file" "Use 85 character line, 60 line page"
.EX "pr \(en3 file" "List \fIfile\fP three columns to a page"
.EX "pr +4 file" "Start printing with page 4"
.PP
.I Pr
formats one or more files for printing.
If no files are specified, \fIstdin\fR is printed.
Options are provided for setting the width and height of the page, the
number of columns to use (default 1), and the page to start with, among others.



